      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, the lambda has to be written in a function that\u0027s got visibility.\n\nYou _could_ follow this pattern, like this:\n\n  template \u003ctypename Ctor\u003e\n  auto make_unique(Ctor\u0026\u0026 ctor) -\u003e \n  std::unique_ptr\u003cstd::remove_pointer_t\u003cdecltype(ctor(nullptr))\u003e\u003e {\n      using T \u003d std::remove_pointer_t\u003cdecltype(ctor(nullptr))\u003e;\n      void* ptr \u003d operator new(sizeof(T));\n      return std::unique_ptr\u003cT\u003e(ctor(ptr));\n  }\n\n  class Foo {\n  public:\n      std::unique_ptr\u003cFoo\u003e makeUnique(float f) {\n          return make_unique([\u0026](void* ptr) {\n              return new (ptr) Foo(f);\n          });\n      }\n\n  private:\n      Foo(float);\n  };\n\nbut it\u0027s kind of easier to do\n\n  class Foo {\n  public:\n      std::unique_ptr\u003cFoo\u003e makeUnique(float f) {\n          return std::unique_ptr\u003cFoo\u003e(new Foo(f));\n      }\n\n  private:\n      Foo(float);\n  };\n\n\n:D",
